         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve"><head>Translation</head><p>Emperor Caesar Trajan Hadrian Augustus, son of deified Trajan, victor in Parthia, grandson of deified Nerva, chief priest holding tribunician power for the fourth time, consul for the third, raised the question of permanent water supply. Quintus Servilius Candidus brought it at his own expense. </p></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>l. 3. trib. pot. IIII - 10 Dec 119 - 9 Dec. 120.</p>
            <p>l. 4.  Presumably a reference to the aqueduct built by Seruilius Candidus, see  <ref type="inscription">357</ref> , ll. 5- 6. </p>
            <p>l. 5. Q. Serulius Candidus. Also in  <ref type="inscription">275</ref> , I. 5;  <ref type="inscription">357</ref> , l. 4;  <ref type="inscription">359</ref> , l. 3.</p>
         </div>
